2026-01-14T02:32:54.644Z [DEBUG] UserCommandMessage rendering: "auto" (args: "proceed with the next steps  Critical Discovery: API Rate Limits

  Issue Found: Kimi-K2 has 4-unit concurrency limit (feather_pro_plus plan)
  - Edge case tests couldn't complete (all timeout at 300s)
  - Confirmed during active session usage + test attempts
  - This is valuable - discovered production constraint before deployment

  Impact:
  - ✅ Single-agent tasks: Work perfectly (9/9 tests passing)
  - ⚠️ Multi-agent scenarios: Will hit rate limits without queuing
  - ⚠️ Extended tests: Need 24h quota reset to run

  Mitigation Documented:
  1. Implement agent queue (max 1 concurrent for Kimi-K2)
  2. Model fallback chain: Kimi-K2 → GLM-4.7 → Llama-70B
  3. Sequential test execution with delays
  4. Feature flag for gradual rollout

and use grep mcp and github mcp to see if there is any code or solutions to this", isSkillFormat: false)

  - ⚠️ Extended tests: Need 24h quota reset to run
